      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You'll want to create characters that reflect the entrenched segregation and white supremacy of the time. The \"good\" folks in your town will be the well-to-do, conservative, and well-educated whites who see themselves as the guardians of tradition and morality. They'll be the ones who own the local businesses, attend church regularly, and look down on anyone who's \"different\" - be it a black activist or a poor white migrant. The activists, on the other hand, will be the idealistic and often naive outsiders who come to town, stirring up trouble and challenging the status quo. You can also include some \"gray\" characters, like the local sheriff or a sympathetic business owner, who might be torn between their loyalty to the community and their growing unease with the injustices of segregation.",
